Staining pattern:
The first three pairs of lateral lappets stain deeply (
Figs 14D,E
); margin of first pair faintly stained, and margin of third pair stains more strongly (
Figs 14D,F
); ventral shields stain from the first one, but the first three shields are slightly lighter that the rest (
Fig. 14E
). Other structures do not stain.
